{
  "text": "Saline had no effect on any of the organ blood flows (Table 3) or regional vascular resistances (Table 4) , which agrees with earlier findings from our laboratory [CITATION_1] . Z1046 produced a dose-dependent decrease in liver blood flow (50 \u03ee 4%, p \u03fd 0.05, after the high dose), which exceeded the decrease in blood pressure so that vascular resistance increased. The low dose of Z1046 did not produce significant vasodilation of the regional vascular beds. In contrast, the high dose of Z1046 produced vasodilator responses in the small intestine (34",
